peer_feedback_assignment_1:
  issue_number: 49
  issue_owner: kevmarcel0
  issue_ok: yes
  issue_status: OK
  overall_comments:
    positive: One notable strength was the organization and structure of the report—the
      author clearly separated the assignment into required sections and used a strong
      mix of inline values, tables, and visualizations to answer the prompts.
    negative: One area for improvement would be expanding the final deliverable section
      to more fully address all three required target demographics and provide more
      detailed interpretation of the results.
    advice: The submission could be improved by completing the full final deliverable
      for all three target demographics, using survey-weighted averages consistently
      throughout the analysis, and adding a bit more polish and interpretation to
      the tables and visualizations.
  scores:
    Written Communication:
      score: 8.0
      comment: It was written well
    Project Skeleton:
      score: 8.0
      comment: Was organized in a clear and understanding way
    Tables & Document Presentation:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The tables are clean, readable, and use gt effectively with appropriate
        titles and subtitles. The document is well-structured and visually easy to
        navigate.
    Data Visualization:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The plots are relevant, readable, and help answer the assignment questions.
        They include clear labels and titles, and the bump plot and age-group analyses
        are especially effective. Additional polish and styling could strengthen them
        further, but they are solid overall.
    Exploratory Data Analysis:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Code Quality:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The code is organized, readable, and generally easy to follow. Variable
        names are clear and the joins and transformations are implemented logically
        throughout the report.
    Data Preparation:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Analysis and Findings:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The analysis demonstrates a good understanding of the ATUS data and
        the major trends in the assignment. The conclusions are reasonable and supported
        by the data, particularly in the sections on household activities, education,
        and childcare time.
    Extra Credit:
      score: 0.0
      comment: he didn't do any
  mp_number: 2
peer_feedback_assignment_2:
  issue_number: 53
  issue_owner: khushwant-khatri590
  issue_ok: yes
  issue_status: OK
  overall_comments:
    positive: One notable strength is how complete and polished the final deliverable
      section is—the three demographic profiles are thoughtful, clearly defined, and
      directly connected to the time-tracking app scenario.
    negative: One area for improvement would be adding slightly more stylistic polish
      and perhaps captions or annotations to a few of the graphs to make the visual
      findings even clearer.
    advice: The submission could be improved by adding more detailed annotations or
      labels to the visualizations and including the second optional extra credit
      item, such as the Apple Watch–style ring visualization.
  scores:
    Written Communication:
      score: 9.0
      comment: The report is very clearly written and organized, with strong explanations
        and smooth transitions between sections. The narrative consistently explains
        why each analysis matters and ties the results back to the larger project
        goals.
    Project Skeleton:
      score: 10.0
      comment: The submission fully completes all required tasks and includes all
        of the required components, including the three target demographic profiles,
        tables, graphs, inline values, AI statement, and the data relationship explanation.
    Tables & Document Presentation:
      score: 9.0
      comment: The tables are polished and easy to read, with effective use of gt,
        good formatting, and clear titles and subtitles. The overall document is visually
        strong and easy to navigate.
    Data Visualization:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The visualizations are informative and relevant, with clear labels
        and appropriate chart types. A few of the graphs could be polished further
        stylistically, but they still communicate the findings well.
    Exploratory Data Analysis:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Code Quality:
      score: 9.0
      comment: The code is organized, well-commented, and easy to follow throughout
        the report. Variable names are clear and the joins, filters, and weighted
        calculations are implemented thoughtfully.
    Data Preparation:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Analysis and Findings:
      score: 9.0
      comment: The analysis is thoughtful and convincing, with interpretations that
        are directly supported by the data. The strongest sections are the discussion
        of demographic differences and the final product-manager style deliverable.
    Extra Credit:
      score: 2.0
      comment: The submission includes the optional data relationship diagram showing
        how the ATUS tables connect, so it should receive the corresponding extra
        credit.
  mp_number: 2
