      comment: The submission includes nearly all of the required components and does
        a strong job addressing each part of the assignment. The structure is complete
        and the final deliverable section is thoughtfully developed.
    Tables & Document Presentation:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The tables are clean, readable, and formatted well with clear titles
        and labels. The overall document is visually organized and easy to navigate.
    Data Visualization:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The visualizations are relevant and communicate the main findings clearly.
        The charts are easy to read and appropriately chosen, although a few could
        be polished further with stronger annotations or styling.
    Exploratory Data Analysis:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Code Quality:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The code is organized and logical, with clear variable names and a
        reasonable workflow. The joins, transformations, and weighted summaries are
        generally implemented well.
    Data Preparation:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Analysis and Findings:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The analysis demonstrates a solid understanding of the ATUS data and
